The paper discusses security schemes in vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs) with cognitive radios (CR), which are related to network infrastructure (NI) and cryptography and security (CR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a cloud computing model for CR-VANETs, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses cooperative spectrum sensing, which is related to systems and control (SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses latency reduction and simulation results, which are related to information theory (IT) sub-category.
